defaultIt is suggested that prisoners do not need access to legal aid for 
defaultthe
default matters
default to be excluded
default because of the availability of complaints procedures. However the Justice Secretary has ignored a large body of evidence,
default including from the Chief Inspector of Prisons, that
default shows that
default the current complaints system is inadequate. 
defaultIt is also suggested that criminal legal aid for prison law can be removed because judicial review remains available.  The reality is that judicial
default review is unlikely to be a desirable or viable option for many prisoners. 
defaultThe ability of prisoners to seek legal advice has been crucial to ensuring that in the closed world of prisons there is accountability for abuse of power.
