defaultUnder the new scope criteriadefault it is likely that D 
defaultwould not be considered for a progressive move, leaving him languishing in closed conditions, at unnecessary public expense.
default&#xa0;
default 
defaultWhy not complain or judicially reviewdefaultIt is unlikely that without access to a lawyer D would even be aware of the cause for 
defaultcomplaint or challenge.  Even if he were aware of this, the complaints system, administered by ordinary prison staff, is not geared up to challenges to serious decisions about the progression of life sentenced prisoners concerning public protection.  Judic
defaultial reviews of decisions by professionals about risk are notoriously complex and deferential to the expert decision makers on the ground.
